The paper proposes an online convex optimization algorithm that achieves optimal regret in the unconstrained setting without prior knowledge of any bounds on the loss functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The algorithm also involves optimization techniques, which could place the paper in the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in proving a lower bound. Finally, the algorithm is naturally hyperparameter-free, which could place the paper in the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
